  "prompt": "Do landlords actually call employers for background checks?",
  "response": "Many landlords do verify employment as part of a background check, but practices vary:\n\n1. Some definitely call employers to:\n- Confirm current employment\n- Verify income\n- Check stability of employment\n\n2. Other landlords might:\n- Only do a basic employment verification\n- Use alternative methods like pay stubs or tax returns\n- Skip employment checks entirely\n\n3. Factors affecting likelihood of verification:\n- Rental market competitiveness\n- Local rental regulations\n- Landlord's personal screening process\n- Property management company policies\n\n4. What most will typically check:\n- Current job status\n- Length of employment\n- Basic income confirmation\n\n5. Tips for applicants:\n- Be prepared to provide proof of income\n- Have recent pay stubs ready\n- Be honest on rental application\n- Have employer contact information accurate\n\nWhile not every landlord will call, many do conduct some level of employment verification, so it's best to be prepared and truthful.",
